    <item>
      <title>Flask and Form Data</title>
      <link>https://textbooks.cs.ksu.edu/cc410/iii-web/17-rest-forms/05-flask-form-data/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://textbooks.cs.ksu.edu/cc410/iii-web/17-rest-forms/05-flask-form-data/</guid>
      <description>Once we’ve built a website that can send form data using an HTTP POST request to our web application, we need some way to access that information in our controller. Let’s look at how we would accomplish this in Flask.&#xA;Flask Path Variables In a previous example, we saw how we can create a route that includes variables directly in the path itself:&#xA;@route(&#39;/greeting/&lt;name&gt;/&#39;) def greeting_with_name(self, name): &#34;&#34;&#34;Display greeting with name.</description>
